\section*{Summary}

\begin{shaded}

\noindent The monitoring of Awak\=opaka skinks is likely to be extremely challenging. This skink species has one of the lowest detection probabilities ever observed. For this reason the initial monitoring design should be undertaken to allow the maximum amount of monitoring flexibilityincluding the use of: count based indices, occupancy methods, N-mixture models, and variable detection mark-recapture. Given the information at hand,  N-mixture modelling and occupancy modelling look to have the greatest potential. It is recommended that a nested spatial approach be undertaken in order to allow for aggregation and redunancy.

\end{shaded}



